# Learn more https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/getting-started-with-git/ignoring-files

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Beehive Pro+ .gitignore
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2026-05-11 (final): Replaced bare "/android" rule with a recursive carve-out
# pattern that ignores all of /android EXCEPT /android/app/google-services.json
# (Firebase config — public identifiers, safe to commit, needed for builds).
#
# Critical detail (learned the hard way): .gitignore syntax does NOT support
# inline comments. Comments must be on their own lines. A line like
#     /android/**                             # (1) recursive ignore
# is interpreted by git as the literal pattern "/android/**[spaces]# (1)..."
# and matches no files. All inline comments on pattern lines have been moved
# to dedicated comment lines.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── Dependencies ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/

# ── Expo build artifacts ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
.expo/
dist/
web-build/
expo-env.d.ts

# ── Native build artifacts + signing keys (NEVER commit these) ─────────────
# Note: these wildcard patterns apply globally — *.jks anywhere in the repo
# is ignored, not just in /android. Keeps signing keys safe even if someone
# accidentally drops one outside the expected path.
.kotlin/
*.orig.*
# Android keystore (private key — NEVER commit)
*.jks
# Apple auth key
*.p8
# PKCS#12 certificate bundle
*.p12
# generic private keys
*.key
# iOS provisioning profile
*.mobileprovision

# ── Metro bundler ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.metro-health-check*

# ── Debug logs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
npm-debug.*
yarn-debug.*
yarn-error.*

# ── macOS metadata ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
# PEM-encoded certs/keys
*.pem

# ── Local environment files (secrets per-developer) ────────────────────────
.env*.local

# ── TypeScript build cache ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.tsbuildinfo

# ── Expo example app scaffold ──────────────────────────────────────────────
app-example

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ── Native folders (Expo prebuild-regenerable, mostly) ─────────────────────
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# iOS — full ignore (we don't track anything in /ios right now)
# If you ever need to track an iOS file, follow the same carve-out pattern
# as /android below (recursive ignore + targeted un-ignore lines).
/ios

# ── Android carve-out pattern (recursive) ──────────────────────────────────
#
# Three rules combine to ignore all of /android EXCEPT google-services.json:
#
#   Rule 1 (line below):  /android/**
#       Recursive ignore of every file at any depth under /android.
#       The ** double-asterisk is the key — single-asterisk * only matches
#       direct children, not nested subdirectories like /android/app/src/...
#
#   Rule 2 (line below):  !/android/app/
#       Un-ignore the /android/app/ directory itself, so Git can descend
#       into it. Without this, the file-level un-ignore in Rule 3 has no
#       effect because Git won't even look inside an ignored directory.
#
#   Rule 3 (line below):  !/android/app/google-services.json
#       Un-ignore the specific file we want tracked.
#
# To add another tracked Android file in the future, add a `!path/` line
# below for each parent directory not yet un-ignored, then a `!path/file`
# line for the file itself.
#
# IMPORTANT: do NOT add inline # comments after the pattern lines below.
# .gitignore treats them as part of the pattern. Comments go on their
# own lines, like this entire block.
/android/**
!/android/app/
!/android/app/google-services.json
